OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44814
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1774947927
OL,3,CVoluntary sector cuts put young people
OL,4,Cat risk, Children's Commissioner warns
OL,6,F"Local Ministers have repeatedly
OL,7,Fcalled on the Westminster Government
OL,8,Fto correct its fundamentally unfair
OL,9,Fapproach in respect of the Local
OL,10,FGrowth Fund. The Executive
OL,11,Fcollectively wrote to Steve Reed, the
OL,12,FSecretary of State for Ministry of
OL,13,FHousing, Communities and Local
OL,14,FGovernment and Hilary Benn, Secretary
OL,15,Fof State, calling on them to reverse
OL,16,Fand change their approach.
OL,18,F"The Executive's Budget remains
OL,19,Fextremely constrained, which continues
OL,20,Fto put pressure on the ability to
OL,21,Fdeliver essential public services.
OL,26,@nD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G14/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44815
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1774947927
OL,3,CVoluntary sector cuts put young people
OL,4,Cat risk, Children's Commissioner warns
OL,6,F"The Finance Minister again reiterated
OL,7,Fthe dissatisfaction with the approach
OL,8,Fof the British Government in a meeting
OL,9,Fwith the Chief Secretary to the
OL,10,FTreasury last week."
OL,12,FWestminster has suggested that the
OL,13,FExecutive could allocate some of the
OL,14,Fadditional funding it has already
OL,15,Freceived from the Treasury to support
OL,16,Fthe voluntary organisations impacted
OL,17,Fby the change.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G15/18
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
